    "introduction-title": "Crafting Mechanic: Logging Expanded",
    "introduction-text": "Welcome to Logging Expanded. Here we'll guide you through the contents of this mod.  To start you'll notice when you cut down a tree, you no longer get Logs, instead you get Tree Trunks. These large, multi-block Trunks contain all the logs you would have cut down from that tree, along side any sticks and resin as well!\n\nFirst, place your Trunk on the ground, and hold <strong><hk>rightmouse</hk></strong> with a knife to Debranch it!  Then you can use an axe to harvest logs and a saw to get boards, but be warned, this is only half as efficient as vanilla Vintage Story!\n\nTo improve your efficiency, you'll want to make a <a href=\"handbook://block-loggingmod:sawhorse-north\">Primitive Sawhorse</a>. This will improve your log and board production. Alongside this, you'll also want to make a <a href=\"handbook://block-loggingmod:splittinglog-oak\">Splitting Log</a>, to produce Firewood with an axe and Support Beams with a saw.\n\nAs you're getting setup, you can store excess sticks using the <a href=\"handbook://block-loggingmod:stickstorage\">Primitive Stick Storage</a> and harvest resin from Pine and Acacia Trunks using a <a href=\"handbook://block-loggingmod:resinrack-fire-north\">Trunk Heating Rack</a>.\n\nOnce you're soldily in the copper age, you can improve your returns by crafting a standard <a href=\"handbook://block-loggingmod:sawhorsestandard-oak-copper-north\">Sawhorse</a> to increase your returns of Boards.  Then, with the arrival of Iron, achieve the highest returns with the construction of an <a href=\"handbook://block-loggingmod:sawhorseadvanced-oak-north\">Advanced Sawhorse</a> and an <a href=\"handbook://block-loggingmod:advancedsplittinglog-oak\">Advanced Splitting Log</a>.  You can also improve your trunk storage and transport by building a <a href=\"handbook://block-loggingmod:trunkstorage-oak-empty-north\">Trunk Storage Rack</a>, which can be carried and transported in Sailboats as well as Carts from the Cartwright Mod!",
    "loggingmod:handbook-category-loggingmod": "Logging Expanded",
    "handbook-category-loggingmod:category": "Logging Expanded"
	
}